[vc_row full_width=&quot;&quot; parallax=&quot;&quot; parallax_image=&quot;&quot; lvca_dark_bg=&quot;&quot;][vc_column width=&quot;1/1&quot;][vc_column_text]The stock market is somewhat unpredictable and volatile, and it’s always liable to react in new and unforeseen ways to the multitude of influences which can sway the prices of different companies in one direction or another. Choosing a security to invest your money into is not an easy task and you have to do a lot of research before making your decision.

Although there are no guarantees that your investment will succeed and deliver superior returns, there are certain ‘rule of thumb’ indicators or gauges which you can use to guide your decision; one of them is history, since history does repeat itself in the markets.

A good investment is not one which is cheap, but rather one whereby you invest in a good company, no matter what the cost of the stock. Good solid companies tend to have good pedigree, they don’t just suddenly appear out of nowhere, and these companies are ones which you can normally trust more than others. The same goes for good industries, since some industry sectors are more reliable than others.

We’ve compiled for you a list of the top 50 companies on the 2016 Dividend Aristocrats List, a list of the companies which have managed to increase their dividends for 25 years or more, and which have therefore proven themselves to be successful through several different economic cycles. It’s also important to note the industry sectors which they fall under, and to note that there are three or four sectors which definitely dominate this list.

